			<h3>History of Codealia</h3>
			<p>Thomas Ochman and Pete Boucher, both members of Agile Ventures, thought up of the idea of Codealia: Where Girls Learn to Code. The project team is comprised of both female and male software developers from all over the world who want to see more women in computer science. </p>

			<p>Codealia.org operates under the MIT License and there is full transparency with all content and materials published on the site. We gear the curriculum specifically to young girls in order to give them an early start in the field of engineering science. Our team proudly uses Agile methods and Ruby on Rails as the framework to deliver well-tested and reliable software.</p>

			<p>Learn more about what we are currently doing on our Facebook page or follow us on Twitter.</p>		
